From 2010 to 2016, a total of 113 588 suspected influenza cases were reported. The majority of cases, 37 551 (33.1%), were reported in 2010 followed by 27 097 (23.9%) in 2015. The total of confirmed cases was 17 094 (15.1%) (

  Table 1
 ). The highest number of confirmed cases were reported in the year 2010, followed by 2015, and the fewest were reported in the year 2013 (

  Figure 1
 ). The majority of cases (96 494, 85%) were suspected cases based on the case definition distributed to all health facilities in Saudi Arabia. Of the 17 094 influenza A(H1N1)pdm09 laboratory-confirmed cases that needed hospitalization, 1780 cases (10.4%) needed intensive care. The largest admission load (9262 cases) was during the year 2015 (

  Table 1
 ).
